# Brute force approach -->
We can create an temporary array, 
We will traverse the entire given array and find out all the non-zero elements and put them in the temporary array.
Then we can put them back into the given array from the first position then rest size of the array will be filled with zero.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(n)$$
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(n)$$ --> Size of the temporary array
# Brute Force Code 
```
class Solution {
public:
    void moveZeroes(vector<int>& nums){
        vector<int>temp;
        int n=nums.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i]!=0){
                temp.push_back(nums[i]);    
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<temp.size();i++){
            nums[i]=temp[i];
        }
        for(int i=n-temp.size();i<n;i++){
            nums[i]=0;
        }
        return;
    }
}
```
# Optimal Approach -->
We can use two pointer approach (i,j).
We will set the value of j = -1
then we will traverse the given array till it finds the first 0. Then the index of it will be stored in j and it will break. After this loop if j remains as -1 then the given array will be returned because it does not contain any element which is 0.
Then a loop will traverse from j+1 to the end of the given array.
Where j will alway be pointing the index of the current 0 and i will find the non-zero element to swap nums[i] and nums[j], when swapping will happen then i and j both will increase. Otherwise only i will be increamented to find the next non-zero element.
# Optimized Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    void moveZeroes(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size();
        int j=-1;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i]==0){
                j=i;
                break;
            }
        }
        if(j==-1){
            return ;
        }
        for(int i=j+1;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i]!=0){
                swap(nums[i],nums[j]);
                j++;
            }
        }
        return ;
    }
};
```
