# Intuition
- when find non-zero element, move it forward until all its previous are non-zero
- searching from front to back, to ensure that its previous is non-zero denotes all its previous are non-zero
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# 🍀 Approach 1
- use for loop to find non-zero
- swap it forward one by one until hit the front or its previous is non-zero
- example: (0-indexed)
  - array: 0 ***0*** ***1*** 2
  - `swap(array[1], array[2]);`
  - array: ***0*** ***1*** 0 2
  - `swap(array[0], array[1]);`
  - array: 1 0 ***0*** ***2***
  - `swap(array[2], array[3]);`
  - array: 1 ***0*** ***2*** 0
  - `swap(array[1], array[2]);`
  - array: 1 2 0 0
  - done
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n^2)$$
    - one worst case is: $$[0, ... 0,1,...,n/2]$$, which totally do swap $$n^2/4$$ times
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code 1
```
void swap(int* a, int* b)
{
  int t = *a;
  *a = *b;
  *b = t;
}

void moveZeroes(int* nums, int numsSize){
  for (size_t i = 0; i < numsSize; i++)
  {
    if (nums[i] != 0)
    {
      int j = i;
      while(j - 1 >= 0 && nums[j - 1] == 0)
      {
        swap(&nums[j - 1], &nums[j]);
        j--;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

# 🤔💭 Follow up: Could you minimize the total number of operations done?
# 🍀 Approach 2
- use a index indicator `head_of_zeros` to store the swap place for non-zero
- use for loop to find non-zero
- swap it with `head_of_zeros`, then adjust `head_of_zeros`
- example: (0-indexed)
  - array: 1 ***0*** ***2*** 0 3 0 0 4
  - `swap(array[1], array[2]);`
  - array: 1 2 ***0*** 0 ***3*** 0 0 4
  - `swap(array[2], array[6]);`
  - array: 1 2 3 ***0*** 0 0 0 ***4***
  - `swap(array[3], array[7]);`
  - array: 1 2 3 4 0 0 0 0
  - done
- therefore, every swap operation does swap the number to the correct place 
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$ , also improved time complexity
<!-- - , because `i` and `head_of_zeros` only move in one direction -->
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code 2
```
void swap(int* a, int* b)
{
  int t = *a;
  *a = *b;
  *b = t;
}

void moveZeroes(int* nums, int numsSize){
  int head_of_zeros = 0;
  bool has_zero = false;
  for (size_t i = 0; i < numsSize; i++)
  {
    if (nums[i] != 0 && has_zero)
    {
      swap(&nums[i], &nums[head_of_zeros]);
      head_of_zeros += 1;
    }
    else if (nums[i] == 0 && !has_zero)
    {
      has_zero = true;
      head_of_zeros = i;
    }
  }
}
