Here is the generic implementation inn Regards to PeekingIterator. 
Basically `<T>` is the generics in the java.
Ref: Java generics javadoc for more details: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/generics/types.html
```
class PeekingIterator<T> implements Iterator<T> {

    private  Iterator<? extends T> iterator;
    T forward;

    public PeekingIterator(Iterator<? extends T> iterator) {
        // initialize any member here.
        this.iterator = iterator;
        this.forward = iterator.hasNext() ? iterator.next() : null;
    }

    // Returns the next element in the iteration without advancing the iterator.
    public T peek() {
        return forward;
    }

    // hasNext() and next() should behave the same as in the Iterator interface.
    // Override them if needed.
    @Override
    public T next() {
        T tmp = forward;
        forward = this.iterator.hasNext() ? iterator.next() : null;
        return tmp;
    }

    @Override
    public boolean hasNext() {
        return forward != null;
    }
}
```

