> Either first call of `peek`, or calls of `next` without `peek` beforehand will move forward the `current` pointer in the given built-in iterator.
> 
> `next` is maintained to tell the first call of `peek`, or calls of `next` without `peek` beforehand.
```
class PeekingIterator implements Iterator<Integer> {

    private Iterator<Integer> iterator;
    private Integer next;

	public PeekingIterator(Iterator<Integer> iterator) {
        next = null;
        this.iterator = iterator;
	}

	public Integer peek() {
        return next == null ? next = iterator.next() : next;
	}

	@Override
	public Integer next() {
        if (next == null) {
            return iterator.next();
        } else {
            Integer toReturn = next;
            next = null;
            return toReturn;
        }
	}

	@Override
	public boolean hasNext() {
        return next == null ? iterator.hasNext() : true;
	}
}
```
